Largemouth bass are easy to catch with smaller minnows or moving bait. To be good to eat, a bass should be right around 12-15 inches, in which this one is. Once they get passed 15 inches, they are a much older fish and their meat is less tasty. The large mouth bass is easy to differentiate because of the wide-set jaw and long back fin. They are very light green in color, and can be found about halfway from the top of the surface of the water to the bottom, where the water is at a cool temperature.
